text.paragraph:
Ambrisentan may cause fetal harm when administered to a pregnant female. Ambrisentan is contraindicated in females who are pregnant. Ambrisentan was consistently shown to have teratogenic effects when administered to animals. If this drug is used during pregnancy, or if the patient becomes pregnant while taking this drug, the patient should be apprised of the potential hazard to a fetus [see 
                           Dosage and Administration (2.2

                           ), Warnings and Precautions (5.1) and Use in Specific Populations (8.1)].
